snippet: Aaron Rodgers practiced this week, raising hopes he might return, but the Packers said they would hold him out of his sixth straight game.
abstract: NFL Roundup; Green Bay Packers will keep injured quarterback Aaron Rodgers on the sidelines for road game against Dallas Cowboys, despite fact that he says he is ready to play; other football news noted.

byline.original: By THE ASSOCIATED PRESS and ZACH SCHONBRUN

lead_paragraph: Aaron Rodgers practiced this week, raising hopes he might return, but the Packers said they would hold him out of his sixth straight game.

headline.main: Rodgers Progresses but Will Sit Another Week
headline.print_headline: Rodgers Progresses but Will Sit Another Week
